Calculator Project

Project Overview
This project is a simple web-based Calculator built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It performs basic arithmetic operations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. The goal of this project is to demonstrate JavaScript event handling, DOM manipulation, and UI design principles.

Tech Stack
HTML5 – for the calculator structure
CSS3 – for responsive and modern interface styling
JavaScript (ES6) – for performing all arithmetic and display operations

Features
Addition, Subtraction, Multiplication, Division
Clear and Backspace buttons
Keyboard input support
Responsive layout with CSS Grid
Error handling for invalid input

File Structure
index.html
styles.css
app.js

How to Run

Download or clone the repository.

Open the folder in a code editor.

Open index.html in any web browser.

Start performing calculations.

Learning Outcomes
Understanding DOM event handling
Implementing mathematical logic in JavaScript
Creating an interactive UI using HTML and CSS
